newsitem.title: USA: Kansas feedlot cattle roundup - USDA.
newsitem.headline: Kansas feedlot cattle roundup - USDA.

text.p: USDA said trade was very slow late Friday. There were not enough slaughter steer or heifer sales confirmed for an adequate market test at the close.

Inquiry and demand were light. Sales confirmed on 400 slaughter heifers Friday. Last week's confirmed sales 125,700 head including 17,600 head or about 14 percent previously contracted or formulated cattle.
Heifers - select and choice 2-3 1075-1100 lbs including some mixed commercial to choice heiferettes 72.00.
